: \"offers\", \"from\": 366, \"to\": 372}, {\"ngram\": \"event\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 379}, {\"ngram\": \"updates\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 391}, {\"ngram\": \"Evening Standard\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 413}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourprivacy notice.\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 442, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourprivacy notice\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 441}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Who could have watched theOlympicsover the past two weeks and not looked within oneself and found oneself wanting?\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 558, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theOlympicsover\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 482}, {\"ngram\": \"oneself\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 531}, {\"ngram\": \"oneself\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 549}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have been awe-struck by the competitors.\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 602, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the competitors\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 601}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Impressed beyond belief by their skill, dedication, and how much they must have sacrificed to get there.\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 707, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"belief\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 626}, {\"ngram\": \"their skill\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 641}, {\"ngram\": \"dedication\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 653}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And scared for them too, because their drive will have caused them harm, and some of the sacrifices they have made may not have been worth it.\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 850, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their drive\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 752}, {\"ngram\": \"the sacrifices\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 807}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am not crying because I have come second, I am crying because it took so much to get here,\\\" saidAdam Peaty, Britain's star breast-stroke swimmer, whomissed out on gold in the men's 100m breaststrokeby a heartbreaking two hundredths of a second.\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 1099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 963, \"end\": 970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.6654948171555344, \"rank\": 0.5026412988148469, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 961}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"a heartbreaking two hundredths\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1086}, {\"ngram\": \"a second\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty, who has spoken openly about his battles with mental health said, \\\"I am an older man here now.\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1106}, {\"ngram\": \"his battles\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1147}, {\"ngram\": \"mental health\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1166}, {\"ngram\": \"an older man\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1191}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not have that relentless pursuit every single day without a sacrifice of some sort.\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1291, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that relentless pursuit\", \"from\": 1217, \"to\": 1240}, {\"ngram\": \"a sacrifice\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1277}, {\"ngram\": \"some sort\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1290}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That sacrifice can come in many ways.\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1329, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That sacrifice\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1306}, {\"ngram\": \"many ways\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1328}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It can come in time, it can come in energy, it can come in relationships.\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1403, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1349}, {\"ngram\": \"energy\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1372}, {\"ngram\": \"relationships\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1402}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It comes in every single form.\\\"\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1435, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every single form\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Who did not brush away a tear watching the great Andy Murray exit elite sport's beautiful, savage stage?\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1486, \"end\": 1497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2781297928547762e-44, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a tear\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1466}, {\"ngram\": \"exit elite sport's beautiful, savage stage\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1540}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Invented by the ancient Greeks in 776 BC when they were held as part of a religious festival at Olympia, the games have no doubt stood the test of time because they show our beautiful, majestic, flawed human condition in all its glory and frailties.\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1561, \"end\": 1575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999993152303048, \"rank\": 5.667728496182898e-07, \"text\": \"ancient Greeks\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1583, \"end\": 1585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 0.999999878117713, \"rank\": 9.167030471693226e-08, \"text\": \"BC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}, {\"begin\": 1641, \"end\": 1648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4445110917424264e-14, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1613}, {\"ngram\": \"a religious festival\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1659}, {\"ngram\": \"the test\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1688}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"our beautiful, majestic, flawed human condition\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1762}, {\"ngram\": \"all its glory\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1779}, {\"ngram\": \"frailties\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1793}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Excellence, determination, hunger for victory, loss and triumph.\", \"from\": 1796, \"to\": 1860, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Excellence\", \"from\": 1796, \"to\": 1806}, {\"ngram\": \"determination\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1821}, {\"ngram\": \"hunger\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1829}, {\"ngram\": \"victory\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1841}, {\"ngram\": \"loss\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1847}, {\"ngram\": \"triumph\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 1859}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All of human life is here, and all of its complications, as we saw withthe awful showdown in the boxing matchbetween Angela Carini andImane Khelif, who has been banned from competing in women's titles by the International Boxing Association.\", \"from\": 1861, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1978, \"end\": 1991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999962103660394, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Angela Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\"}, {\"begin\": 2069, \"end\": 2101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.686469990255749e-21, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"human life\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1878}, {\"ngram\": \"its complications\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1916}, {\"ngram\": \"withthe awful showdown\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1950}, {\"ngram\": \"the boxing\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 1964}, {\"ngram\": \"women's titles\", \"from\": 2047, \"to\": 2061}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a highly charged scene at the North Paris Arena where Carini was struck by multiple powerful blows, she surrendered after just 46 seconds and fell to her knees sobbing.\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2142, \"end\": 2147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.511299470046869e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2160, \"end\": 2166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piero_Carini\", \"score\": 0.9760276891015702, \"rank\": 0.024561097155633066, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piero_Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piero_Carini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a highly charged scene\", \"from\": 2106, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple powerful blows\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"just 46 seconds\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2243}, {\"ngram\": \"her knees\", \"from\": 2256, \"to\": 2265}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not fair,\\\" she said, \\\"It's not fair.\\\"\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2318, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Has life been fair for Khelif either; is it ever?\", \"from\": 2319, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2327}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 2342, \"to\": 2348}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Scenes of amazing human drama like this have united us all at a time of national friction as we gather around televisions and cheer on athletes who we have often never heard of.\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2547, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Scenes\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2376}, {\"ngram\": \"amazing human drama\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2399}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2424}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 2432, \"to\": 2438}, {\"ngram\": \"national friction\", \"from\": 2442, \"to\": 2459}, {\"ngram\": \"televisions\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2491}, {\"ngram\": \"cheer\", \"from\": 2496, \"to\": 2501}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And those of whom over the years we have become familiar with, and fond.\", \"from\": 2549, \"to\": 2621, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the years\", \"from\": 2572, \"to\": 2581}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Who would not cheer for star gymnastSimone Biles, who, after a troubled last Olympics in Tokyo has, on what she describes as her \\\"redemption tour\\\", won a stunning three gold medals in Paris; as she teaches us that it's possible to dazzle sometimes, and sometimes you fail, too.\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2712, \"end\": 2717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9992467691389494, \"rank\": 0.0007537984699074109, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2807, \"end\": 2812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.511299470046869e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"star gymnastSimone Biles\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"a troubled last Olympics\", \"from\": 2684, \"to\": 2708}, {\"ngram\": \"her \\\"redemption tour\", \"from\": 2748, \"to\": 2768}, {\"ngram\": \"a stunning three gold medals\", \"from\": 2775, \"to\": 2803}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2829, \"to\": 2831}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympics 2024 LIVE!\", \"from\": 2902, \"to\": 2921, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympics\", \"from\": 2902, \"to\": 2910}, {\"ngram\": \"LIVE\", \"from\": 2916, \"to\": 2920}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sky Brown in action; Team GB miss out on equestrian medal; Josh Kerr later; Day 11 latest Paris Olympics 2024: Adam Peaty cries 'happy tears' despite missing out on 100m breaststroke gold Simone Biles: how she became the greatest gymnast of all time Olympics 2024: Andy Murray 'genuinely happy' after bidding farewell to tennis on own terms Or the pathos of watching Brit heroAndy Murray's glittering careerdraw to a close on Thursdayas he and Dan Evans were knocked out in the Olympic men's doubles quarter-finals.\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 3441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2943, \"end\": 2950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999959073, \"rank\": 4.256699691733501e-12, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2963, \"end\": 2973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9999422229755119, \"rank\": 5.777397937010539e-05, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}, {\"begin\": 3013, \"end\": 3027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\",